𝘿𝙚𝙩𝙖𝙞𝙡𝙚𝙙 𝙀𝙭𝙖𝙢𝙥𝙡𝙚𝙨 ::

  :: 𝑰𝒏𝒄𝒓𝒆𝒎𝒆𝒏𝒕 𝑶𝒑𝒆𝒓𝒂𝒕𝒐𝒓 (++) ::--

     >> 𝙿𝚛𝚎-𝙸𝚗𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚎𝚗𝚝 :- The value is incremented before it is used.

         int a = 5;
         int b = ++a;             // First increment 'a', then assign to 'b'.
         System.out.println(a);   // Output: 6
         System.out.println(b);   // Output: 6

     >> 𝙿𝚘𝚜𝚝-𝙸𝚗𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚎𝚗𝚝 :- The value is used before it is incremented.

         int a = 5;
         int b = a++;             // First assign 'a' to 'b', then increment 'a'.
         System.out.println(a);   // Output: 6
         System.out.println(b);   // Output: 5

  :: 𝑫𝒆𝒄𝒓𝒆𝒎𝒆𝒏𝒕 𝑶𝒑𝒆𝒓𝒂𝒕𝒐𝒓 (--) ::--

     >> 𝙿𝚛𝚎-𝙳𝚎𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚎𝚗𝚝 :- The value is decremented before it is used.

          int a = 5;
          int b = --a;              // First decrement 'a', then assign to 'b'.
          System.out.println(a);    // Output: 4
          System.out.println(b);    // Output: 4

     >> 𝙿𝚘𝚜𝚝-𝙳𝚎𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚖𝚎𝚗𝚝 :- The value is used before it is decremented.

          int a = 5;
          int b = a--;             // First assign 'a' to 'b', then decrement 'a'.
          System.out.println(a);   // Output: 4
          System.out.println(b);   // Output: 5


